# Load Order And Manifests

- Treat `MuniganXCT.toc` and the project `include.xml` files as startup manifests where ordering is part of runtime behavior.
- Only add a file to TOC/XML when it must load at startup, and place it in the correct stage of the addon boot sequence.
- Keep `core.lua` after `include.xml`; it assumes config, libs, media, and modules are already loaded.
- Verify every referenced path exists exactly as written. A stale `<Script file="..."/>` or TOC entry can break the addon at load time.
- Avoid reordering bundled library includes unless the change is intentional and validated; Ace3 and shared-media dependencies are load-order sensitive.
- If you introduce a new module, wire it into the smallest relevant manifest instead of dumping everything into the root TOC.

Example: adding `modules/myfeature.lua` should usually mean registering it in `modules/include.xml`, not directly in `MuniganXCT.toc`, and confirming the file exists in the repo.
